## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Rated at 52.5° ESN (42.5° Japanese), but plays and feels much closer to a 48°-50° rubber.
    - Feedback: Clear and highly communicative. You know exactly where the ball hit the blade.
    - Hold vs. Release: It holds the ball beautifully on brush-loops but releases it rapidly on flat drives.
    - Dwell Time: Medium-High. The softer upper layer of the dual sponge wraps the ball before the hard bottom layer fires it back.

- Sound/Click
    - Loud and immensely satisfying. Produces a sharp, pronounced click that Tensor lovers adore.

